Be armed against such obscurities rather by submission than foreknowledge. The knowledge of future evils mortifies present felicities, and there is more content in the uncertainty or ignorance of them. This favour our Saviour vouchsased unto Peter when He foretold not His death in plain terms, and so by an ambiguous and cloudy delivery damped not the spirit of His disciples.
